00:37:31,150 --> 00:37:34,290
The Amityville Horror,
The Philadelphia Experiment,

658
00:37:34,291 --> 00:37:37,650
organic food myths,
Bigfoot, spirit orbs.

659
00:37:37,651 --> 00:37:40,987
There's something in here
to challenge everyone.

660
00:37:44,450 --> 00:37:47,233
Some people criticize science
by pointing out that it

661
00:37:47,234 --> 00:37:50,016
does not know
everything and doesn't have all the answers.

662
00:37:50,017 --> 00:37:51,927
Obviously, this criticism is true.

663
00:37:51,928 --> 00:37:55,053
Science is all about the fact that we don't know everything.

664
00:37:55,500 --> 00:37:58,050
Science is the learning process.

665
00:37:58,500 --> 00:38:01,189
If we want to improve the world, improve

666
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:03,879
the human condition, improve technology;

667
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:07,980
learning, and thus science,
is the essential way forward.

668
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:11,239
When your hear someone criticize
science because it

669
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:13,878
doesn't have all the answers, don't
argue with them;

670
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:17,500
instead point out that that's the central strength of science.

671
00:38:17,501 --> 00:38:20,250
We couldn't be learning more every day

672
00:38:20,251 --> 00:38:22,999
if we presumed to
already know everything.

673
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:25,985
Some people criticize skepticism

674
00:38:25,986 --> 00:38:28,050
because it doesn't
leave well enough alone.

675
00:38:28,551 --> 00:38:30,367
Many paranormal and alternative beliefs

676
00:38:30,368 --> 00:38:32,184
bring comfort to those who practice them,

677
00:38:32,185 --> 00:38:35,818
and are a positive force in many
peoples' lives.

678
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:39,264
But happiness and enlightenment
are all around us in our world;

679
00:38:39,265 --> 00:38:42,328
you don't have to turn to
pseudoscience to find them.

680
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:45,972
And moreover, once we begin investing our faith

681
00:38:45,973 --> 00:38:49,144
in unsubstantiated
or supernatural phenomena,

682
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,006
we are contributing to the
redirection of attention,

683
00:38:52,007 --> 00:38:57,100
influence, and funding
away from technologies and concepts

684
00:38:57,101 --> 00:38:59,241
that have been evidenced to be

685
00:38:59,242 --> 00:39:01,382
beneficial to humanity and to our world.

686
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:05,212
The choice between pseudoscience and science

687
00:39:05,213 --> 00:39:08,625
is the choice between
stagnation and progress:

688
00:39:09,150 --> 00:39:13,575
progress toward long
life, health, happiness,

689
00:39:13,576 --> 00:39:18,000
a cleaner planet, bountiful
food, knowledge, and peace.

690
00:39:19,870 --> 00:39:23,317
There may indeed be
undiscovered dragons in our world.

691
00:39:23,318 --> 00:39:25,909
But there is also
something we know for a fact:

692
00:39:25,910 --> 00:39:28,500
we haven't
found any dragons yet.

693
00:39:28,816 --> 00:39:32,480
We've looked in a lot of places,
and seen some extraordinary things;

694
00:39:32,650 --> 00:39:36,240
but never yet has science been forced
to throw in the towel

695
00:39:36,241 --> 00:39:39,830
and admit the reality of magic.

